    "department": "Customer Success / Professional Services",
    "description": "About the Company\n\nWhy We Built Lyric: Supply chains are more critical and complex than ever. Every day, large enterprises navigate trillions of possible decisions that could impact the bottom line. Powerful algorithms and AI can address these problems, yet most organizations struggle to leverage supply chain AI at scale. The current SCM technologies are either rigid, limited-scope point solutions or custom solutions built in-house, which demand immense expertise and investment.\n\nThat is…until now.\n\nEnter Lyric: Lyric is an enterprise AI platform built specifically for supply chains, offering the best of both worlds:\n\n - Out-of-the-box AI solutions for optimizing networks, allocating inventory, scheduling routes, planning fulfillment capacity, promising orders, propagating demand, building predictions, analyzing scenarios, and more, plus\n\n - A platform-first approach that empowers both business and technical users with end-to-end product composability, leveraging no-code tools, their own code, or even forking our code to build and refine supply chain decision intelligence\n\nWith Lyric, enterprises no longer have to choose between flexibility and speed, they get both.\n\nThe Mission: We’re building a new era in supply chain with the team best equipped to lead it. With over 20 years at the intersection of supply chain and algorithms, we developed a deep conviction that global supply chains needed something like Lyric. Since our inception in December 2021, that conviction has been validated time and time again.\n\nToday, a growing number of Fortune 500 companies, including Smurfit WestRock, Estée Lauder, Coca-Cola, and more, are innovating on their own terms with Lyric. We can’t wait to see what our customers, both current and future, are empowered to build with us next. Come build with us!\n\nAbout the role\n\nLyric is hiring a Senior Delivery Lead for Product Training based in Chicago, US. This is not a traditional training role; it’s for someone who believes supply chain is the most compelling applied AI problem in the enterprise.\n\nAnd for us, AI means two things:\n\n - Algorithmic Intelligence: optimization, simulation, probabilistic forecasting, inventory mathematics, constrained planning\n\n - Agentic Intelligence: AI copilots, decision agents, workflow automation, systems that reason and act\n\nIf you are someone who is energized by both the math and the machine reasoning layered on top, this role could be a great fit for you.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nDeliver \u0026 Build\n\nYou will build. Not just present.\n\n - Lead immersive workshops across North America\n\n - Facilitate technical modeling sessions\n\n - Build lightweight starter models that demonstrate real decision impact\n\n - Support onboarding and pre-sales enablement\n\nTranslate Complexity into Clarity\n\nYou’ll take concepts like clustering, optimization, demand sensing, and AI agents, and make them intuitive and actionable.\n\nYou’ll help customers understand not just what the system does, but how to think with it.\n\nScale Learning\n\n - Develop repeatable training modules and playbooks\n\n - Build structured product curricula\n\n - Integrate new AI capabilities into enablement\n\n - Continuously refine content based on field feedback\n\nWe’re building a learning engine, not decks.\n\nWho you are\n\nYou likely have 8+ years of strong experience in demand, supply, inventory, or network planning.\n\nMore importantly:\n\n - You build: models, tools, frameworks, systems\n\n - You’re excited about both optimization-based AI and agent-driven AI\n\n - You’re comfortable leading executives and going deep technically\n\n - You balance deep work with a fierce desire to communicate clearly\n\nBonus:\n\n - Experience with optimization or AI-driven planning tools\n\n - Experience training enterprise customers on complex platforms\n\nEven if you don’t meet 100% of the qualifications, we recommend applying to the role!\n\nLocation: Hybrid - Chicago, US or open to relocation. Some travel (25%+) is required for customer + partnerships training.\n\nComp: The annual compensation range for this position is $165,000- $185,000 base cash. Base cash will be determined based on years of experience, with an additional 20% variable compensation that is earned based on individual \u0026 business performance. You will also receive equity in Lyric.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
